androidx.appcompat.widget

Class ActionMenuView

  • java.lang.Object
    • ViewGroup
      • androidx.appcompat.widget.LinearLayoutCompat
        • androidx.appcompat.widget.ActionMenuView
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MenuBuilder.ItemInvoker, MenuView

    public class ActionMenuView
extends LinearLayoutCompat
implements MenuBuilder.ItemInvoker, MenuView
    ActionMenuView is a presentation of a series of menu options as a View. It provides several top level options as action buttons while spilling remaining options over as items in an overflow menu. This allows applications to present packs of actions inline with specific or repeating content.

        protected ActionMenuView.LayoutParams generateDefaultLayoutParams()
        Description copied from class: LinearLayoutCompat
        Returns a set of layout parameters with a width of android.view.ViewGroup.LayoutParams#MATCH_PARENT and a height of android.view.ViewGroup.LayoutParams#WRAP_CONTENT when the layout's orientation is LinearLayoutCompat.VERTICAL. When the orientation is LinearLayoutCompat.HORIZONTAL, the width is set to LayoutParams#WRAP_CONTENT and the height to LayoutParams#WRAP_CONTENT.
